Cladophora prolifera
is widely distributed in tropical and warm-temperate seas, both in the Atlantic and Pacific Oceans, as well as in the Indian Ocean ( Taylor 1960 ; Hoek 1963 & 1982 ; Hoek & Womersley 1984 ;
Silva et al. 1996
). However, this species seems to be rare on the coast of Japan ( Hoek & Chihara 2000 ). This is the first record from Piauí and Alagoas.
